\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 PART 8 \'97 IMPORTANT BUSINESS RULES TO ENFORCE IN CODE\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 1.No self-referral. When processing an enrollment with a ref code, verify that the referral code does not belong to the enrolling user.\
2.No circular referrals. Before building the upline chain, verify that the new pro does not already appear anywhere in the referrer's upline chain.\
3.Homeowner confirmation required. processJobCommissions must only run when homeownerConfirmed = true. Never calculate network income on unconfirmed jobs.\
4.Activity gate. Before adding an upline pro to the payout list, check that jobsCompletedThisMonth >= 2. If they are below the threshold, skip their payout row \'97 do not pay them, but do not break the chain (the next level up still gets paid if they are eligible).\
5.Subscription gate. If subscriptionActive = false for an upline pro, skip their payout row.\
6.Unique address check. The homeDocumentation table uses a SHA-256 hash of the normalized address. Only the first pro to document a given address earns the $0.25 credit. Subsequent pros documenting the same address get isFirstDocumentation = false and originationCreditAmount = 0.00.\
7.Payout threshold. When running end-of-month disbursements, only process payouts where the recipient's total pending amount is >= $50.00. Roll forward smaller amounts.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
